<p>This collection is open for research.</p><p>Many collections are housed offsite; retrieval requires advance notice. Please <extref xlink:href="https://libraries.indiana.edu/lilly-library/ask">make an appointment</extref> a minimum of one week in advance of your visit.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <bioghist id="aspace_b9b253cab32cfaaf5c258b1bdc57ba1e">
    <head>Administrative History</head>
<p>Randall House Rare Books is a bookselling firm in Santa Barbara, CA, run by Ron Randall and Pia Oliver since 1980. The company grew out of the San Francisco firm Randall and Windle, opened in 1975 by Ron Randall and John Windle.</p>  </bioghist>
  <arrangement id="aspace_879b3a5a1830a7ff26104d382b6b4d00">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>The collection is arranged into the following series: I. Paid Bills; II. Miscellaneous; III. Appraisals; IV. Books for Sale; V. Book Descriptions; VI. Inventories.</p>  </arrangement>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_36f286d988c719f87fa6ddd75b2b86fd">
    <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
<p>The Randall House mss., 1975-2013, consist of the business records and correspondence of the San Francisco bookselling firm Randall and Windle, and of its successor Randall House. Included are ledger sheets, paid bills, payroll records, correspondence, and tax records and receipts.</p>  </scopecontent>
